                            <comment id="17033512" author="beobal" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2020 11:44:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When creating the read commands &lt;em&gt;after&lt;/em&gt; setting &lt;tt&gt;gcgs&lt;/tt&gt;, the &lt;tt&gt;nowInSeconds&lt;/tt&gt; wasn&apos;t being bumped far enough. It was only adding 1 to the value used for the inserts. This could lead to a race where occasionally a tombstone was not yet purgable. Fixed by bumping it a full 60s as in the other similar tests. No failures seen running this 200 times locally.&lt;/p&gt;

